  <!--
    AbstractSession's protected backing fields (createTime, endTime, returnCode, ...) collide with
    the properties generated from their getters. This file used to carry a remove-node rule per
    field; they are gone because they achieved nothing measurable. Removing the fields here and
    letting the generator skip them produce byte-identical generated code, and the rules only
    trade the generator's BG8401 "duplicate field or property name" warnings for the same number
    of BG8A00 "matched no nodes" ones. BG8401 is suppressed in the .csproj instead.
  -->

